UPDATE post SET BODYTEXT='<h2>What is Spingular?</h2>
<ul>
<li>It is an open source and collaborative project made with Jhipster.</li>
<li>It is a live project that it is explained in its GitHub project. Explained? What do you mean? Whether you are a beginner that wants to find out an example about how to <a href="https://github.com/Tonterias/jhipsterpress/blob/master/ReadMe/Solution1.md" target="_blank"> How to open access to the REST Api:</a> or a more advance user who wants to see <a href="https://github.com/Tonterias/jhipsterpress/blob/master/ReadMe/Solution20.md" target="_blank"> How to change DTOs to load attributes of not related entities:</a> and see the actual code working, just visit the <a href="https://github.com/Tonterias/jhipsterpress" target="_blank"> ReadMe file at GITHUB</a></li>
<li>And YES, you can use it for your own website.</li>
<li>At the same time Spingular will try to create a community for Jhipster developers to join groups about different topics such as Websockets, Mapstruct, or anything you like. The community groups will develop what the group wants. For example, I would like to create a chat made with Ionic for Spingular and a Microservive version of Spingular. Join me in those groups if you want to learn how to do it.</li>
</ul>
<br />

<h2>So, what is inside Spingular?</h2>

<p>The App is the combination of several sub-apps or parts: a newspaper with a blog and a meeting site (or grouping site). Let us start with a brief description of each part:</p>

<ul>
<li>Newspaper: The admin can manage the FrontPage of the site placing news that he considers interesting. This news can be general news, or specific ones about main interests or activities that are important for his or her gorup. A profile or a group can have a Blog, post news and users can comment those posts that would be grouped with tags and topics that are related with the interests and activities of the meeting site.</li>
<li>Meeting site: A user can fill a profile detailing the activities or interest he has. He can follow other user with similar tastes, activities or programming interests, to join groups that meet together. A user, or group profile, can upload an Album with photographs. A profile can also receive messages and notifications.</li>
<li>TODO: Spingular in Microservices: It is a must, is not it?.</li>
<li>TODO: Spingular Chat: let start with creating a chat that looks great on you mobile phone using IONIC.</li>
<li>TODO: Proposals: Think of a proposal as a general idea. A user thinks about something that wants to show or bring forward to other fellow programmers for consideration, so he fills a proposal. This proposal could be explained in a Post and it can be voted by other users, a group or the general visitor.</li>
<li>TODO: Bulletin Board: will be used to post offers and demands for things or services.</li>
<li>Other ideas: I have a few more ideas, but first I would like to start with the ones already mentioned here.</li>
</ul>
<p>It is really up to you. <a href="http://www.spingular.com/#/post/16/view">Read the post: Welcome to Spingular</a>, join the groups and start learning about the things you need to practice with.</p>' where id>=1;





UPDATE post SET BODYTEXT='<h2>Welcome to the Spingular Project</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As you already know&nbsp;Spingular, is an open source and collaborative project made with Jhipster (take a look at <a href="http://www.spingular.com/#/post/15/view">what Spingular is</a>) to find out more. So, how can we organize a community to maximize what you get as an individual programmer from your collaboration and what the group gets as a whole from you? First thing, the group should listen to what you want to say or do. You probably have your experience and I do have mine, so we can enrich each other exchanging them. Therefore, we are open to your ideas! Of course, there will be rules, otherwise it will not work. Some of those two strict rules are education and compromise. You will demand them from other, so it is fair to be ready to give the same back.</p>
<p>We will have to define together how to reward your personal efforts and group efforts.</p>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>So, who is Spingular Project for?</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I am sure I can tell who is NOT for. If you are the hell of a programmer, this is not for you, right? You should be part of the team that makes the code for Jhipster and collaborate with them and collect&nbsp;the bounties!</p>
<p>If you want to learn about things in  real life examples, this is the place! Why? Because you want to climb this ladder to be a top programmer, but you are not at the top of the hill yet.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2>Starting point of the ladder.</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I'm not a programmer (actually I have a BA degree but always fascinated by computers), so I have the point of view of the unexperienced.</p>
<p>I learned Spring (thanks to a great teacher: John Purcell&nbsp;<a href="https://caveofprogramming.com/" rel="nofollow">https://caveofprogramming.com/</a>) and Angular (with a course from Maximilian Schwarzm&uuml;ller:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udemy.com/the-complete-guide-to-angular-2/" rel="nofollow">https://www.udemy.com/the-complete-guide-to-angular-2/</a>). Then I learned Jhipster with these books and the help of Jon Ruddell:</p>
<ul>
<li>The JHipster Mini-Book 4.5 by Matt Raible. Now with a chapter on microservices!</li>
<li>Full Stack Development with JHipster by Deepu K Sasidharan and Sendil Kumar. Get it on Packt and Amazon.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.safaribooksonline.com/library/view/full-stack-development/9781788476317/" rel="nofollow">https://www.safaribooksonline.com/library/view/full-stack-development/9781788476317/</a>&nbsp;A must read cause I'm going to explain things that are not fully enough covered there.</li>
</ul>
<p>This is the fastest way to get up and running that I know of, so this is the first step of the ladder. Anyone who reads these books should have, at least, the same level as I have.&nbsp;Spingular will offer you examples and solutions for the problems that are not covered in the books or the courses.</p>
<p>You will find all the steps of the ladder in those books, courses and the solutions to the problems that a real app like Spingular has which will be available in the <a href="https://github.com/Tonterias/jhipsterpress">GitHub repository</a>&nbsp;in order of difficulty (or as we have encountered them). Check them out before going on.</p>
<p>We will need to know what is your actual level so you will not get bored or throw the towel. This is very important!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Second step of the ladder.</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>What do you want to do? Microservices? Kubernetes? Functionality in the app? Testing? Deployment? Let us know. Here is the incomplete list of <a href="https://www.spingular.com/#/post/2/view" target="_blank">Spingular's Project List</a>. Let us know what you want to see on the list. Use your profile extensively. Take <a href="https://www.spingular.com/#/uprofile/5/view" target="_blank">my profile</a> as an example of how to help anyone find out what do you like or want to do</p>
<p>If you are not interested in Monolithic apps then it will be demotivating to tell you that you have to do Monolothic apps. On the other hand, Spingular will NOT work if nobody does the unpleasant part of the job. So, you will have to choose what to do and you will probably have to do some unpleasant part of the job too.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Other steps of the ladder.</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We will find out together. This is alive! Once your profile is complete <a href="https://www.spingular.com/#/message/new?uprofileIdEquals=5" target="_blank">Send me a Message</a> to let me know that you are ready to start. It will take time to find other members to make a team and it does not matter whether you are a pro or just learning, it matters if you want to learn and work</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Last step of the ladder.</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As any open source project, please help yourself and use it as much as you need it. Recognize the work of others, when ever it is posible. Like in other projects where everything is free, donations are welcome. If you find Spingular useful recognize it and if you want to donate, please contact us.</p>' where id=16;
